cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless communication networks for high-speed trains, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses MIMO technique for improving the quality of service, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with communication networks for high-speed trains, which is a subfield of communications and networking. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a two-hop model for resource allocation and access control, which can be related to multiagent systems. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with improving the performance of a system (high-speed railway communication), which can be related to systems and control.
